===message:kevin, while i agree with your point about the sucessfulness and importance of this war, i disagree on a few things.  one, the civil war itself did not end slavery. slavery (while not in the degree it once had) still continued in some ares in the south. slaves having no where to go or any education many times stayed with their masters. slavery is like a running faucet, while yes the civil war did acomplish turning it "off" some drops still continued to fall.  two, are you sure it was 500,000 persons who were lost in the civil war? i could have sworn that it was 600,000 but in a time where not many records were kept i guess there might be a lot of conflicting numbers.
