===message:You may be correct about the total number of deaths in the Civil War I was merely estimating.  The lives lost was not meant to be the focus of my discussion.  Secondly, we can not use one event and say that this particular action ended slavery.  Slavery faded off of a number of years after the war, but to use a event in history that undoubtedly began the process it would have to be the war. No, all the slaves were not "free" immediately after the war but the war was critical in ending the institution.
